text: Kalawao County is a county in the U.S. state of Hawaii. The county encompasses the Kalaupapa or Makanalua Peninsula, on the north coast of the island of Moloka ªi. The main village is Kalaupapa. Kalawao County is the smallest county in the United States by area. It does not have its own government. Category:1905 establishments in Hawaii Category:Hawaii counties
